HEADWORD: Almagra
<hw>Al*ma"gra</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>almagra</ets>, <ets>almagre</ets>, fr. Ar.
<ets>al</ets>-<ets>maghrah</ets> red clay or earth.]</ety> <def>A fine,
deep red ocher, somewhat purplish, found in Spain. It is the
<altname>sil atticum</altname> of the ancients. Under the name of
<altname>Indian red</altname> it is used for polishing glass and
silver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

